{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, when the line flux is magnified only for some velocity bins while others are demagnified, e.g.",
    "the blue wing of the line is magnified while the red wing is demagnified.",
    "The method also fails when some velocity bins are more (de-)magnified than the underlying local continuum.",
    "A description of the method when both absorption and emission lines are present can be found in Hutsemékers et al. (2010).",
    "If applied to pairs of spectra that have not been corrected by the time delay, intrinsic variability could mimic microlensing-induced line deformations, and/or chromatic microlensing."
  ]
}